Q7 - Who is the stakeholder? Who are you, Mr Femmer?
Answer: The stakeholder is a customer, his name is Professor Henning Femmer who has money to build the system. He is a methodology expert, not manager or boss, just an expert who organizes community like team meetings. He has a team that consists of a bunch of Requirement Engineers (RE), they are the users who conduct elicitation during the RE process. He needs a tool to assist his RE teams. 
 
Q8 - What would be the goal of this tool? Maybe the main goal?
Answer: To guide and support the stakeholder’s RE in supporting asking right questions (interview) that will save time, from interview to specification takes forever and this tool should fix it. 

Q9 - What are further information about this tool you would like to add?
Answer: Interruption during an interview could also happen. The tool is like a mentor or consultant, who could at the right moment, give recommendations to ask follow up questions. Maximum 4-5 people during one interview. Needs approval, needs a log of changes in interview, who is accessible to the developer,  not only the ‘project log’. Like in normal interview, they used have one or two hour meeting, but the summary of the interview are sometimes insufficient, so the tool needs to create as much as a summary that are valuable to the whole team. Tools make suggestions based on discussion between interviewers, and the suggestions always have references to which part of conversation/discussion being made. The tool which was empowered by the intelligence layer might recommend so many suggestions that might be too much, so the tool needs to be able to connect the pattern of the issue, so that there will be no unnecessary repetition. Tool should stick to live meeting, but there is option to deactivate live feedback, the live direct feedback feature is default though. Tools should handle conflicting suggestions and be able to ask follow up questions.  If there is a wrong transcription or feature, he doesn't need an advanced feature like user’s rating, instead the stakeholder would just have a follow up meetings with ‘users’ which is his RE teams, the tool itself is not meant to replace the whole framework or responsibilities. The database (interview transcript) should be somewhere local, not cloud,, actually he doesnt really care! :) he said: People approve hallucination requirements; this has to be avoided, this is the worst case. This will jeopardize the ‘main goals’. He said: The meeting is just like business usual, the financial department, like 2-5 people. Sometimes large workshops happen as well, but today that is rare. Build it before regular team meetings. 
